Safaricom chief executive officer Bob Collymore has been named international business leader of the year at the 9th annual Africa Investor awards.The giant telecommunications firm, which has aligned its corporate strategy to the United Nation's Sustainable Development Goals, has deployed significant resources to facilitate national development. Business leaders have the unique opportunity to drive change that can transform not just economies, but whole communities. More than any other group, the private sector has the ability to accelerate inclusive growth and drive sustainability at great speed and scale, said Collymore after receiving his award.Nigerian entrepreneur and philanthropist Tony Elumelu was honored as Africa Investor Person of the Year, while the CEO of South Africa s Public Investment Corporation Dr Daniel Matjia was feted as the African Institutional Investment Personality of the Year.